@startuml
title Full Workflow: Feature Lifecycle (End-to-End)
skinparam style strictuml
skinparam sequenceMessageAlign center
skinparam noteFontSize 11

actor Student as S
participant "GitWizard" as W
participant "Git" as G
participant "GitHub" as R
actor Teammate as T

== Option 1: Start Feature ==

S -> W : Option 1
W -> R : Fetch open issues
R --> W : Issue #2: [BR-02] Edit Community
S -> W : Pick issue #2
W -> G : checkout main, pull,\ncheckout -b feature/BR-02-edit-existing-community
G --> W : Branch created
W -> S : "Go to your IDE"

note over S : Student implements\nfeature + tests\nin IDE

== Option 2: Save Progress (repeat as needed) ==

S -> W : Option 2
W -> S : "Run mvn clean verify?"
S -> W : y
W -> G : mvn clean verify
G --> W : BUILD SUCCESS
W -> S : "Stage all? (A/S)"
S -> W : A
W -> G : git add .
W -> S : "Issue number?"
S -> W : 2
W -> S : "Commit message?"
S -> W : "Add validation to Community"
W -> G : git commit -m\n"Add validation to Community #2"
G --> W : Committed

note over S : Student continues\nworking, repeats\noption 2 as needed

S -> W : Option 2 (again)
W -> G : git add . && commit\n"Add unit tests for validation #2"
G --> W : Committed

== Option 3: Submit for Review ==

S -> W : Option 3
W -> G : git push -u origin\nfeature/BR-02-edit-existing-community
G -> R : Push branch
R --> G : Branch uploaded
W -> R : gh pr create\n"Implement edit community (BR-02)"
R --> W : PR #35 created
W -> S : "PR created! Ask for review."

== Team Review ==

S -> T : "Please review PR #35"
T -> R : Read diff, leave comments
T -> R : Approve PR
R -> R : GitHub Actions CI passes

== Option 4: Merge & Cleanup ==

S -> W : Option 4
W -> R : gh pr view #35
R --> W : APPROVED, CI: SUCCESS
S -> W : Merge PR #35
W -> R : gh pr merge 35\n--merge --delete-branch
R --> W : Merged
W -> G : checkout main, pull,\ndelete local branch
G --> W : Clean state on main

== Option 5: Create Release Tag (on release day) ==

note over S : After all features\nfor R2 are merged

S -> W : Option 5
W -> G : git tag -a R2\n-m "Release R2"
W -> G : git push origin R2
G -> R : Tag published
W -> S : "Release tag R2 created!"

note over R
  Instructors evaluate
  the tagged version:
    git checkout R2
end note
@enduml
